Research titled ?Experiences of Adolescents Receiving a School-Based Intervention to Improve Resilience ? a Qualitative Study?, in partnership with professors and researchers from the University of Kent, under supervision of Prof. Patricia Wilson.
This research is part of a Big Loterry fund project (https://www.biglotteryfund.org.uk/HeadStart) to support young people to cope with adversity. It has been implemented in different ways across Kent (http://www.kent.gov.uk/education-and-children/headstart) East Kent was selected for investigation, which implemented the Penn Resillience Programme (PRP; J. E. Gillham, L. H. Jaycox, K. J. Reivich, M. E. P. Seligman, & T. Silver, 1990). This is a cognitive-behavioural intervention designed to prevent depression in adolescents. Acess was obtained to one primary school, to year 6 students, aged 10-11.
